					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Even in the linked thread, you could see that making this repro might lead to the person becoming interested in NES development, and making further things. It's like with people writing emulators, first trying to get their favorite games working, then becoming interested in accuracy for its own sake. Do you have links to more threads from the past showing that people asking for this information are just a drain on this board? Even if they are, locking and banning people might have unintended side-effects that are worse than those of these people being allowed to post and get replies. I just don't see a big problem, and would like some evidence.</div>

